-- Keyed presence probe. Attestations are partitioned LIST(type_id) ->
-- HASH(subject_id); `id` is NOT a partition key, so the old id-only join
-- could never prune -- every probed id paid one index descent per leaf
-- (~145x read amplification; measured 2026-07-16: 4.2M ids in 1.2s against
-- empty leaves -> 165s at WordNet scale, growing with substrate size).
-- The caller computed each attestation id FROM (subject, type, object,
-- source, context), so it always holds the partition keys: binding the type
-- to a plpgsql variable prunes the LIST parent at plan time, and the
-- subject equality prunes the HASH leaves per row -- one descent per id.
-- ONE PASS (2026-07-21). The previous body looped over the DISTINCT relation
-- types in the batch and re-unnested the FULL three arrays inside every
-- iteration, discarding all but that type's share via `WHERE u.t = v_type` --
-- O(N_ids x N_types) row materializations for O(N_ids) of actual work.
--
-- MEASURED on the OMW seed: one backend pinned at 100% of a single core for
-- 5m28s with 4.1 GB RSS while 11 cores sat idle, stalling the whole ingest
-- inside this probe. Cost is quadratic in the batch's type diversity, so it is
-- invisible on single-type batches and lethal on a multilingual source that
-- touches many relation types at once.
--
-- The loop bought nothing. Its stated purpose was to bind the type to a
-- plpgsql variable so the LIST parent prunes at plan time -- but this is a
-- SELECT, and runtime pruning IS available to reads: with the type joined
-- per row, the nested-loop inner Append prunes to the single matching leaf at
-- execution (verified: `Append (rows=8) (actual rows=1.00 loops=32000)` on the
-- sibling merge path). Plan-time pruning is only load-bearing for UPDATE,
-- whose target result relations are opened and locked at plan time -- which is
-- why attestation_merge still needs its EXECUTE-with-literal and this does not.
--
-- Joining u.t directly keeps the same per-row LIST+HASH descent, one pass, one
-- plan, and lets the planner parallelize.
DROP FUNCTION IF EXISTS attestations_present_ordinals(bytea[]);
CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION attestations_present_ordinals(
    p_ids bytea[], p_type_ids bytea[], p_subject_ids bytea[])
    RETURNS TABLE(idx int)
    LANGUAGE sql STABLE PARALLEL SAFE
    SET search_path = @extschema@, public AS $$
    SELECT (u.ord - 1)::int
    FROM unnest(p_ids, p_type_ids, p_subject_ids)
         WITH ORDINALITY u(id, t, s, ord)
    JOIN attestations a
      ON a.type_id = u.t               -- runtime LIST prune per row
     AND a.subject_id = u.s            -- runtime HASH-leaf prune per row
     AND a.id = u.id
$$;
